OL,3,CBBC insist Adams allegation
OL,4,Ccoroborated by a total of six sources
OL,6,FAt the High Court in Dublin on Friday,
OL,7,FMr Adams's barrister Tom Hogan SC
OL,8,Fbrought forward a witness with
OL,9,Fknowledge of journalistic standards to
OL,10,Fprovide an opinion on the contents of
OL,11,Fthe programme and accompanying website
OL,12,Freport.
OL,14,FJohn Martin O'Loan told the jury that
OL,15,Fit was his opinion there was no
OL,16,Fevidence in the programme or article
OL,17,Fthat the BBC corroborated the
OL,18,Fallegation that Mr Adams had
OL,19,Fsanctioned the killing of Mr Donaldson.
