OL,7,Fthe BBC statement on other sources.
OL,9,FAsked if he was telling the court that
OL,10,Fhe had decided to deliberately exclude
OL,11,Fthe information because he deemed it
OL,12,Fto be irrelevant, Mr O'Loan said what
OL,13,Fwas in his report was about the
OL,14,Fprogramme and that the information
OL,15,Fabout the additional sources was "not
OL,16,Fcredible".
OL,18,F"If I left things out, it was
OL,19,Fdeliberate. It was all a deliberate
OL,20,Fview based on my background as to the
OL,21,Fprocess to publication."
